<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Title</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:300,400,600,700,800&display=swap&subset=latin-ext"
          rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<style>
    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    }

    ul {
        list-style: none;
    }

    .intro-siemplify {
        background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,');
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        width: 1000px;
        height: 560px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        color: #CCCCDA;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
        grid-template-rows: auto minmax(auto, 1fr);
    }

    .intro-siemplify__close {
        grid-column: 1/3;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: flex-end;
        padding: 30px 25px 12px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__left {
        padding-left: 46px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__right {
        padding-left: 50px;
        font-size: 13px;
        color: #0F1029;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__right--content {
        overflow: auto;
        height: 435px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__right--footer {
        height: 80px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__left--title {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 30px;
        padding-right: 40px;
        margin-bottom: 25px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__left--list .item {
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__left--list .item a {
        cursor: pointer;
        font-weight: normal;
        font-size: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .intro-siemplify__left--list .item .link.active {
        box-shadow: 0 1px 0 #CCCCDA;
        font-weight: bold;
        padding-bottom: 2px;
    }

    .content-section h2 {
        margin: 40px 0 0 0;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 16px;
    }

    .content-section li {
        margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .content-section img {
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .section-one-container h2 {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    ::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
        background-color: transparent;
    }

    ::-webkit-scrollbar {
        width: 12px;
        height: thin;
    }

    ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
        border-radius: 10px;
        border: 3px solid transparent;
        background: #49495E;
        background-clip: content-box;
    }

    ::-webkit-scrollbar-corner {
        background-color: transparent;
    }

</style>

<body>

<div class="intro-siemplify">
    <section class="intro-siemplify__close"></section>
    <section class="intro-siemplify__left">
        <div class="intro-siemplify__left--title">Siemplify Version 5.3.0</div>
        <div class="intro-siemplify__left--list" id="introTabs">
            <ul>
                <li class="item">
                    <a class="link active" data-target="sectionOne">Playbook Blocks</a>
                </li>
                <li class="item">
                    <a class="link" data-target="sectionTwo">Data Retention Options</a>
                </li>
                <li class="item">
                    <a class="link" data-target="sectionThree">Python 3.7 Support</a>
                </li>
                <li class="item">
                    <a class="link" data-target="sectionFour">View Only Users</a>
                </li>
                <li class="item">
                    <a class="link" data-target="sectionFive">Playbook Fallback Branch</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="intro-siemplify__right">

        <div class="intro-siemplify__right--content">
            <div class="content-section section-one-container" id="sectionOne">
                <h2>Playbook Blocks</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"
                             alt="">
                    </li>
                    <li style="padding-right: 140px;">
                        <p>Users can now create small standalone playbooks called blocks and then use these blocks to
                            create complete playbooks.
                            <br><br>
                            This approach eliminates the need for users to update a large
                            number of playbooks when something in their environment changes (for example a security
                            control is changed).
                            <br><br>
                            With this block-based approach to playbooks, the time required to
                            create and maintain playbooks is significantly reduced.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section section-two-container" id="sectionTwo">
                <h2>Data Retention Options</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"
                             alt="">
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Users can now define how long to retain data to meet their specific needs.
                            <br>
                            This period can be set per-environment or for the entire system.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section section-three-container" id="sectionThree">
                <h2>Python 3.7 Support</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"
                             alt="">
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Siemplify now supports Python version 3.7</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section section-four-container" id="sectionFour">
                <h2>View Only Users</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"
                             alt="">
                    </li>
                    <li style="padding-right: 100px;">
                        <p>Organizations can now purchase View Only licenses enabling anyone to access the
                            Siemplify Security Operations Platform for viewing purposes only.
                            <br><br>
                            This license is especially useful for enterprises looking to provide dashboard access
                            only for external stakeholders or managed security service providers (MSSPs) who
                            wish to provide direct access to their customers.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section section-five-container" id="sectionFive">
                <h2>Playbook Fallback Branch</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"
                             alt="">
                    </li>
                    <li style="padding-right: 90px;">
                        <p>Users now have the ability to manage Playbook failures with pre defined logic by choosing a
                            default Fallback Branch. This guarantees Playbook completion and ensures a more seamless
                            experience for the analyst.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="intro-siemplify__right--footer"></div>

    </section>
</div>

<script>
	let links = getAnchors();
	for (let i = 0; i < links.length; i++) {
		links[i].addEventListener('click', onLinkClick);
	}

	function onLinkClick(event) {
		setActiveClass(event.target);
		scrollToDiv(event.target);
	}

	function scrollToDiv(anchor) {
		const targetDiv = anchor.dataset.target;
		const div = byId(targetDiv);
		div.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
	}

	function setActiveClass(anchor) {
		const anchors = Array.from(byClassName('link'));
		anchors.forEach(anchor => anchor.classList.remove('active'));
		anchor.classList.add('active');
	}

	function byId(id) {
		return document.getElementById(id);
	}

	function byClassName(name) {
		return document.getElementsByClassName(name);
	}

	function getAnchors() {
		return byClassName('link');
	}
</script>

</body>

</html>
Subject: 5.3 Announcement
